Former rivals Chris Brown and Drake have squashed their feud and are teaming up for a new collaboration on Brown’s upcoming album, Indigo. “No Guidance”, one of the 37 tracks on the record, will feature Drake and also include features from H.E.R., Justin Bieber, Lil Jon, Lil Wayne and the Nicki Minaj and G-Eazy collab, “Wobble.” Brown hinted at the collaboration when he shared a photo with Drake, who he recently dubbed Aubreezy on Instagram with the caption, “SUMMER TIME BOUT TO GET ALOT HOTTER!”   SUMMER TIME BOUT TO GET ALOT HOTTER! A post shared by  CHRIS BROWN (@chrisbrownofficial) on Jun 5, 2019 at 4:06am PDT  Recall the duo began feuding back in 2012 over Rihanna, and in June of that year, the two and their friends began throwing bottles at each other at NYC’s W.i.P. nightclub over a note that allegedly read “I’m f—ing the love of your life.” The duo squashed their beef and performed on stage together during Drake’s “Aubrey and the Three Migos Tour” last year at the Staples Center in Los Angeles. Since then, they’ve been spotted out together. Brown’s Indigo is out June 28.